article.headline: James Madison 82, E. Kentucky 71
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Terrance Carter had 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead five players scoring in double figures Wednesday night as James Madison beat Eastern Kentucky 82-71. Juwann James and Abdulai Jalloh scored 15 apiece for the Dukes (4-1), and Kyle Swanson and Heiden Ratner had 12 each. James also had 10 rebounds as James Madison outrebounded the Colonels (2-4) 41-22 and shot 50 percent from the field. Mike Rose led Eastern with 21 points, 17 in the second half, and Darnell Dialls added 15 points. The Colonels tied the score three times in the second half, but couldn't get any closer than five in the final 14 minutes. Eastern raced out to an 18-7 lead, but the Dukes responded with a 21-6 run that turned the deficit into a 28-24 lead with four minutes left in the first half. Carter scored seven of his nine first-half points during the spurt. James Madison pushed the margin to 37-27, but the Colonels scored the last five points of the half to trail 37-32 at the break.
